{
  "text": "The theory of wavelength-controlled irregular phased arrays is well described in Ref. [CITATION_1] , and the main results are given in the following. The interelement spacing d r and the optical path difference n c \u232cl r \u0351\u232cl r = l r+1 \u2212 l r \u0352 between adjacent waveguides should satisfy",
